    <section id="sect-00002">
    <title>Encapsulation</title>
    <para id="para-00004"><term id="term-00002">Encapsulation</term> is a key concept in OOP that involves wrapping data and procedures that operate on that data into a single unit. Access to the unit's data is restricted to prevent other units from directly modifying the data. Ex: A ticket website manages all transactions for a concert, keeping track of tickets sold and tickets still available to avoid accidental overbooking.</para>
