    <section id="sect-00003">
    <title>Abstraction</title>
    <para id="para-00007"><term id="term-00003">Abstraction</term> is a key concept in OOP in which a unit's inner workings are hidden from users and other units that don't need to know the inner workings. Ex: A driver doesn't usually need to know their car engine's exact, numerical temperature. So the car has a gauge to display whether the engine temperature is within an appropriate range.</para>
